caption: Wow, the food is DELICIOUS!!!!!!  the avocado salad was so fresh and refreshing. will definitely be returning
Great food, generous portions, good prices and the best service!

I have always wanted to try the food here but after doing delivery apps during the pandemic out of desperation because I lost my job and this currently is my only means of income and seeing how they treat drivers who are there to serve THEIR customers I have lost interest. The manager who is running the place is extremely rude and mean. Typically it is a hassle to even receive the order and I usually end up unassigning. I will only accept orders from this place as a last resort if I need the money and am having a bad night. You, sir, and your mistreatment and rudeness towards customer service workers, have lost a potential customer and any support for this establishment! It doesn’t hurt to show a little bit of kindness. We’re all struggling here, and making people’s jobs and lives harder for them than it already is doesn’t help. Try and grow some empathy and decency towards other people! Shame on you!
Great food, can get pretty busy
Gave me food poisoning 😡

I ordered the sushi box and it arrived completely different than the first time i ordered it. It came with spicy mayo on it (which it does not have) and no eel sauce, fish eggs, or wasabi sauce which is suppose to be on it. It was also not rolled properly and came with the smallest sliver of fish. It also only had 8 pieces when normally it comes with 10. After explaining to the waiter that it was not the roll I ordered, they refused to remake it and told me I was wrong even though I have ordered it many times and showed a picture of what it normally looks like. The food also gave my friend and I food poisoning. Will not be coming back.
There is no social distancing
The food and the sake was very good. Will go back and try more things on the menu!
Wonderful Ambience,, Great Asian fusion food ... Just love this ❤️
Get the lunch special. It's cheaper than Publix and better too.
Wonderful very decently priced food and the service is amazing.

Ok this place is amazing! Not only are the prices great but the food and service was wonderful! I got the lunch deal which is your choice of two rolls (I got the crunchy spicy tuna and it was sooo good) but it also came with a soup and salad for only 8 dollars! The house made ginger salad dressing was really good. They also had a great selection of tea. Honestly this place is 10/10 and I can’t believe how empty it was! Gainesville is sleeping on this fantastic restaurant! Sad I don’t live there because I would definitely eat here all the time.
Great drinks and good and friendly service.

I love everything they have. From the soup, to their sushi, its all very good. I've probably had the entire menu over the years and yet to be disappointed by any of it. The portions are great if you like big dinners like myself. If you're a steak lover, try the sirloin, or ribeye. Always cooked perfectly!
Service was excellent.  The food was very good.  Really enjoyed the experience!

Please be careful with the pan-seared escolar. It was a delicious dish, but I ended up with a waxy diarrhea after eating it. I then found out that escolar is known to cause this (keriorrhea) due to the natural indigestible waxy esters in the fish. You can Google it or search on Pubmed. While the fish is not deemed toxic or lethal when prepared appropriately, I do wish that I was told about the keriorrhea side effect before I decided to try this fish out...
My favorite dish at Liquid Ginger is the pad Thai. I love the location and atmosphere. The service is always good . I would recommend!
I so enjoyed our lovely meal and dinner.it was all absolutely delicious.

Ordered three different regular sushi roles to go. I could never imagine sushi being this bad. They were made of weird meat mush and bread crumbles without any veggies I think. They were just so bizarre. Maybe go for the fancier ones. Tho preparation and pick-up was fast.
Very friendly staff. Great sushi
Disappointed. Had eggplant but cooked too much and like mush.  Also had green too and not hot enough.

Ordered takeout and the food was okay, I didn't order any sushi which might be better than the chicken and calimari (don't order, it was chewy and didn't taste fresh.). I'll be willing to come again but for the price I think I'd rather eat somewhere else.
Always my to go place. Has really nice food. My Fav is Panang coconut curry.
Great Asian fusion at really good prices. The sashimi was huge pieces. The bento box option is a strong value. This is a favorite when we visit Gainesville.

Nice atmosphere, clean environment, good vibes, but subpar service.  Took about 15 minutes after sitting down before a waiter tended to us with water and another 10 mins before we could get anyone to take our orders. We were very understanding of the given circumstances with the lack of service, but it shouldn’t have been that slow in a restaurant with 6 tables filled. We ordered a sushi and sashimi for two platter and a martini which ended up have a fruit fly. We did get a replacement, but the bartender didn’t seem too happy. Portions are a bit skimpy for the price, but I guess the environment makes up for it. Bathrooms are a bit dark in the ladies room with buckets in the way.  Not for or against another visit. If I ever go again, I hope it makes up for the mistakes.

Liquid Ginger has THE BEST specialty rolls in all of Gainesville!! The Tuna Amazing, Angry Dragon and Snow White rolls are our favorites. Even my BF was impressed with the Gator roll and he's not the biggest sushi fan. Customer service is beyond superb, also! If they make a mistake, they go above and beyond to make it right. Glad we have this hidden gem in Gainesville!!

Nice staff, good food, fair prices. I particularly like the Gator Roll with no cream cheese. I find it comparable to the Dragonfly Classic Roll. Used to be a die hard DragonFly fan, but can get comparable food at lower prices and less packed at Liquid Ginger!
Very bed serves and food!!!!!
The staff was super nice and the food was amazing
We ordered for the first time last night for my husband's birthday and it was absolutely amazing!! Everything was so delicious and top notch. We can't wait to order take out here again!! Yummy!!!

Deserted for lunch but the service was just right and the establishment was clean and beautiful. The speed of the meal coming from the kitchen was quite quick. The food was very well prepared and presented. Quiet relaxed atmosphere while there is quite a shopping plaza outside. Beautiful architecture all around and brick streets that now serve as walk ways with sculptures to view out of the windows while you dine.
Great lunch specials and awesome service.  Food is yummy.
Amazing food and service!
Good variety of menu items.  Great service.   Discounted drinks: $2.50 for a good martini!
Great food. Large menu.
Lovely restaurant, clean and professional. The servers are accurate and polite. Every dish I've seen served here is wonderfully presented and really full of flavor and technique.
Delicious food!

Whitney was an incredibly awful waitress. My friends wanted to share a sushi roll and she came back 20 minutes later asking what roll they wanted because she forgot and then returned 45 minutes later saying the roll could not be made even though my friends have eaten this roll many times before. They ended up ordering different rolls which she managed to mess up. We also asked 4 times for sides of spicy mayo and eel sauce and she never brought it so we asked the water person to bring it for us. She was very defensive about her screw ups and we are very disappointed about the service. She also put the wrong orders on each of our bills.

I have steamed dumplings as appetizer. Sushi box for main course.  Yummy & beautiful presentation. Located in downtown Gainesville by community Plaza, theater, restaurants.  A pleasant walking district.  Parking could be challenging but there are city parking garages nearby.
Great food, great service, great prices!
The food was amazing! Service was very good too, highly recommend.

One of the best spots for lunch or dinner in Gainesville, period. You can order any food or drinks on the menu, and you will be pleased. I especially recommend the teriyaki beef and lime salad dressing. Get the $5 bento box upgrade for dinner. Service is on point, too. Other Gainesville Asian restaurants (Samurai in particular) are just jokes in comparison.
Great food from a huge menu. The service was outstanding too.
Excellent restaurant for dinner with friends and family. Delicious food too. Nice sized portions, good enough to share.

Loved the tasting menu of small plates which range in price from $5 to $10. We had the deep fried Japanese Oysters which were excellent. We then split the Grilled Lobster Bento Box which contained 2 -6 ounce lobster tails, rice, and several vegetables. Everything was delicious. Our server was excellent. I did not give it 5 stars because we sat for a very long time before a server was assigned to our table. 17 minutes. Employees kept passing us by as if we weren't there. No water on the table, nothing. Once we were assigned a server, everything went very smoothly.
Excellent food!! One of my favorite placed to eat!!
Best sushi ive had in a long time, and probally best in Gainesville
Great lunch specials
The dragon roll was great and the pricing not bad at all. Our server, Andy was awesome!
Best lychee martini I've ever had. Always tasty. Come with soup and salad. Great tea. Good prices especially at lunch.
Bad service...
Amazing night out. Thank you so much for the great service. Yummmy happy birthday to me, i love sushi.
Great place
Great fusion Asian cuisine, surprisingly good ribeye steak?!
One of few sushi places offering riceless
Good food at a good price. Generally, not ok busy like some of the trendy places around it. I prefer it to other restaurants in the same area.
Like the vibes of the restaurant. The food was good and had no issues. Pretty nice date spot. Will go again because they have a lot of food options
Grest food, Poor customer service. Bad service undermines the quality of food.
I wish I could subtract stars...The server obviously did not want to be there. Ruined my daughter's 16th birthday with rudeness and HORRIBLE service. Don't waste your time or money!!!!!!!!!!!
Delicious food light and tasty. Quiet atmosphere

I went for lunch today, and, as always, the food was great. Their lunch specials are amazing! I got Pad Thai for $8.00, which included soup, salad, a spring roll, and a cup of rice, which I didn't even need.  My lunch partner got the Thai curry for the same price.  I've had the garlic eggplant in the past,  which is also excellent.  Fast service, and friendly staff. Pretty decor, and outside seating is also available.  They are often busy, but it's a great atmosphere! Always a great experience!
Best beef curry. Miso soup so good and ginger salad.
Excellent in every way.
(Translated by Google) Delicious salmon, very friendly service  (Original) Salmón delicioso, muy simpático el servicio

Food and service were both very good. The only drawback was a very loud table of 10 people.  Hot tea selection was huge. Tuna roll with peppered tuna was exceptional.  The spicy kani krab roll was very tasty. Lobster roll was good, spicy mayo was heavy, ask for it on the side if you don't like alot.
One of the best Asian fusion restaurants in town. Awesome food and service.
Service was great waits weren't long, overall was very good.
Food was excellent and so was the service. Great evening!!
Nice vegetarian options and decent prices. I loved the tofu pad thai
Tasty food with large portions.
I totally enjoyed my food and the service was the  best. Next time i visit , my friend and i will have the Bento Box..my neighbord steak looked yummy. Thank you for an enjoyable dinner.
Fusion of flavors. Everything is always fresh. Customer service is ok
Always such good food and service here!!
One of my favorite places for lunch.  Sushi is very good and fresh.

My wife and I went for the first time an anniversary dinner. The food and drinks were excellent and the entire serving staff was very attentive. We will definitely go back to try some of the other appetizers and sushi since we only had entrees this time.
The service was great and so was the food!
Good sushi yo. Drinks are ok.
Good food. Good service. Would recommend.
The tea is a great addition to the meal, and the liquid ginger roll is definitely a win.

I used to order lunch from Liquid Ginger all the time---the sushi is not amazing, but it's not bad and the lunch prices cannot be beat. However, after my 2 most recent experiences I will not be giving this business my money any longer. Their lunch comes with a soup and a salad. Recently, they have not been giving me the salad. I always ask for it politely, and the host usually apologizes and gets it, but the last two times I was confronted by the owner and told it was my fault they didn't give me a salad. He was very rude both times and basically gaslit me about my own order. He launched into two different very long convoluted explanations both times. It was so weird and made me really uncomfortable. I just wanted my tiny little salad! I see that other people have had bad service experiences here, and I honestly think it's because the owner is a really strange, mean guy. I think they probably treat their employees terribly. I'll be steering clear even though it's convenient.  P.S. I did recently notice that they use CONSIDERABLY less fish (specifically spicy tuna) in their lunch rolls, as I ordered one at dinner.

My fiance took me here for our anniversary dinner and it was quite lovely! The food was delicious, the drinks were reallu great. I got the dancing shrimp Sushi roll, oh, so good! The only bad thing was the server was pretty inattentive.
There is literally only one word for this restaurant: AMAZING Sosososososooo good and (to be honest) better than dragonfly (which is across the street from Wyatt's coffee).
Food is pretty good, drinks are good. Service is mostly lackluster. No bad attitudes or anything, just lack of caring, ie. waiters don't check up on you, etc.
Good veg options!
A really place for a romantic dinner
good sushi
Excellent food, good atmosphere,  good service.
Great sushi & lunch place!

This place is my GO TO! during the week the do a lunch special where you get 3 rolls for 12$ or 2 for 9$ and it comes with soup and salad. It’s amazing! Their sushi is delicious and not pricey at all! I would definitely recommend this place to anyone.

The food is Bland and even when I tried to add seasonings and spices it just didn’t help. Good service til the woman who took my order gave me a rude look when she decided to listen in on my conversation. Over all it’s was about a 2/3 stars max.
BAD SERVICE, great food and beautiful location!
Decent food. Very nice wait staff. The seats in our booth we beyond horrible...like sitting in cotton candy, minus the sticky. But yes, decent food.
The wait, though...
Don't bother. Try chopsticks. Or if it is. Or Bangkok Square. Wait is too long and doesn't live up
Randomly walked over. Dragonfly had a 2 hour wait. Food was delicious and came out quickly/well prepared.  I now prefer Liquid Ginger over Dragonfly.
Fantastic tea, great food, large portions, low cost. What more could you ask for? It’s a clean restaurant and I’d recommend it to anyone in town.
Delicious!  Friendly waitress, fast service and great environment
Great food, service and reasonable prices.
Considering that the prices are reasonable, this place was pretty good. Service was good.
By far the best restaurant in Gainesville FL!

I was pleasantly surprised.  Comfortable and relaxing seating.  The place was full but not noisy.  I don't take that for granted anymore.  The service was great.  Very attentive staff.  We shared sushi, I had a bulgogi bento and my wife had the salmon.  Every bite was delightful.  Yes sir.  We liked it.
Delicious and has several vegetarian options

GREAT FOOD!! Go at lunch time. The prices are WAY less expensive than the dinner menu!! 2 sushi rolls for $9 or 3 for $12 and there's a variety to choose from. Also, their lunch meals come with soup and salad and you won't leave hungry!!!
Good not amazing lil higher priced good atmosphere
The food was ok, but it took almost 45 minutes to come out and was luke warm. We were also one of two tables there, so it was not busy or anything.
Great place to eat and I especially love their ginger dressing. The spicy soy shrimp is A1

Wow. Everything good. Jasmine tea and the way it is served was authentic and such a great experience. The food outstanding. The staff attentive, knowledgeable, and friendly. Will be a favorite of mine whenever in Gainesville.
We love liquid ginger!! The service is fast, and food is awesome. Huge selection of drinks, sushi, and entrees. We’ve never disliked what we ordered off the menu. Highly recommend.
Best service if you have a reservation but prices are good food is good
Nice, quiet sushi spot in downtown. They also have a large selection of hot teas.

Very, very good Soshi American style. The service is fair and very kind, the food is excellent and never disappoints and it is fair priced (rolls $4-$15). Great location, more upscale feel, and quiet environment.
Best sushi place in Gainesville
Service is amazing and fast. The food is well presented and scrumptious. The smiling face of Adam Rogers makes it all even better. Thanks for a wonderful experience.

Asian cuisine, steaks and seafood prepared in an elegant setting.  There is an expansive cocktail menu and the prices are shockingly low given the quality of the food.  I highly recommend the bento upgrade, the soups and salad are tasty and the red bean ice cream is well worth a try.  The only downside is it is quite busy at peak hours, reservations are recommended.
Romantic atmosphere, great customer service and delicious sushi!
Best Chocolate Martinis and best price!

I have never been more disappointed than with my meal tonight. 10 years ago this was a staple of Gainesville fine dining, but the food tasted like it was cooked yesterday. My girlfriend got filet mignon that was chewy and bland. My sushi was tough with almost no filling. Overall I couldn't recommend going here to anyone unless you only want a dumpling.
Love the lunch, the price, 3 courses, real china and silver, excellent taste.

Love the ginger glazed salmon with a great char on coconut rice.  Also the wonderful loose leaf tea selection served over warmers in iron teapots. Great unique place to meet friends, bring guests from out of town.
The Fusion Ribeye is by far one of the best steaks in Gainesville.
Very slow service. Not a lot of food for the price you pay. Food was luke warm at best. Wife couldn't even eat hers, it had a very nasty taste.
Sushi rice was over cooked! Disappointed !!!
Fabulous and fresh food! Lunch shrimp entree is only $8 with soup, salad and veg egg roll.
Excellent food and service

I had their Thai Curry on the lunch menu and the food was okay but the portion, especially the curry soup was rather skimpy. I had expected to get something with more soup given some of the photos others have posted but it was really little. The waiter taking out a check and putting it on the table only when I was halfway done was dampening. I’ll probably not go back but the place was clean and food was ok so I am giving 3/5 stars.

Yummy cocktail, not as impressive food. I loved everything except the entree. My Pad Thai tasted like a mixture of ketchup and peanuts and my boyfriend's veggie sautee was extremely bland. The wakame and tofu square apps were delicious, though, and the atmosphere was great. Our waiter, Adam, was rather rude. He seemed annoyed any time we asked a question and looked at us like we were dumb for asking if they had spicy mustard or to simply add broccoli to the vegetable sautee. He also gave us our bill without asking first after disappearing for long periods of time. 2 or more of us wanted dessert...and it was a good hour before they even closed. I'm usually pretty understanding having been a server myself, but the mix between our unpleasant waiter and the very mediocre entree dropped my rating down to average. The appetizers and cocktails are what kept it above a 2-star, and honestly, the sushi my friend got looked amazing. In the end, though, for the price you pay, it wasn't worth it to me and I don't plan on returning here.

I went to the Liquid Ginger Restaurant a few months ago with a group of ladies, the staff was very helpful in making sure we had everything we needed to have a good event dinner. The food was very delicious and quantity and quantity was good. Everyone enjoyed the evening and their meals. I would recommend Liquid Ginger Restaurant for a group event dinner or dinner for two or more for any occasion. Ask for the private dining room, if you are having a group dinner or meeting or event, it makes for a very nice place for any small event.
Great Sushil

Has some of the best steak I've ever had, I guess depending on the cook. I've had enough of them to not rate the steak perfect but when it's cooked properly, top 5... hell top 3. Their sushi is meh, so is their drinks but I'm quite fond of their fried potstickers. The soup, salad, and ice cream that comes with the bento box add-on is all really good as well.
Food wasn't really perfect
Excellect food, drinks and atmosphere. If you want Asian fusion food this is the place to go. From Sushi to Krispy fish this is my favorite place in Gainesville.

Food and service was very good. The only thing that I thought was a bit lower class was the nickel and dime attitude of  .75 for a side of sauce in a restaurant that cost $50 per person.  It is not a money issue but the point.
Very delicious food!
I haven’t been in a while, but the coconut cream shrimp makes sure I’ll be back. Amazing food. A gem in Gainesville.

My wife and I had our wedding rehearsal dinner here 1.5yrs ago. It was awesome then. But tonight we spent $40 for food we could not eat. Scallops were bland and raw, the chicken and rice was hard as a rock, and soup that was way to salty. The staff was awesome without a doubt, no offense to them. They were kind, and attentive. But we really did not want to finish our meals and left shortly after getting our food.
One of my favorite places to eat in Gainesville. The food is always great and I lpve the atmosphere. Service can be slightly la king sometimes, but overall its a great place.
Great food, staff, and very clean restrooms.

I went to the Liquid Ginger a couple of weeks ago, with a group of high school friends, we all had a great time and the food was delicious. The staff was friendly and helpful. The manager made sure everything was set up perfectly. Thanks for everything everyone did to make our evening turn out well. I would definitely recommend Liquid Ginger for any event or evening out. Our event was well organized and the food was delicious, the quality and the quantity was great. I will definitely go back. Below is a pic of only one section of the menu. Everything we ate was delicious!
Relaxed low key quiet atmosphere with great food. Full bar, a variety of Sake!
Good overall menu
Great place to meet and greet.. The Sushi is outstanding!
Good place for larger group dinners
The appetizers on my favorite part of the menu. The sushi is OK it's not the best in town. The lunch specials are OK you get what you pay for.
Very good food. Service was a bit on the sloppy side, maybe because we went around closing time.
Great pan-Asian food! Huge menu with plenty of options in addition to a well-stocked tea menu. Waitstaff is quick and happy to help with the menu.
Quality food, great service, reasonable prices
The ambiance is great, but service was very slow and I couldn't taste the tamarind in my pad Thai.
Love this place

The three times I have ordered food from here the dishes have been incredibly bland, and the flavors have been generally off. I am a big fan of Thai food, and as there aren’t many Thai places in the downtown area I gave this place two tries with two different dishes (the second was Pad Thai because I figured that’s a classic), and I am not sure that I have been more disappointed by Thai food either time. So, I decided I would give their sushi a try. Gainesville has great sushi, and this place is just not up to snuff. The spicy mayo was an odd white color and had a completely liquid consistency. I have never seen sloshy, white spicy mayo elsewhere. I don’t normally write bad reviews, but I gave this place a lot of chances and in the end it was a waste of money. Do not recommend.

Okay, so dinner was great. No complaints on the food. Atmosphere was nice. We went on Valentine's day, so I can understand being busy, and there being a wait for sushi orders, and having a new server in training, and the possibility of being short on sushi chefs, and even our party forgetting about it after our bottle of plum wine and a good main course, BUT.... I really wish we would have received our Black Dragon sushi plate that was ordered and paid for. I bet it would've been yummy. Other than that; 4, possibly 5 stars.
Fresh ingredients, with imagination.
Not bad dishes, but very small portions
Delicious, decent price
Good food...good prices and good ambience
Favorite place to eat asian fusion food in town. Love the menu, and the bento boxes. Special shout out to the avocado salad and their ginger dressing.

We went in on a Thursday night (1/11/2018), it was slow. The place was dead, there were 3 hosts and about 3 servers. We sat down around 8pm, opened our menus, and this blonde girl brought out water, got uncomfortably close to me with her eyes wide open and asked "Hi theeeere! How are yooou?". By the way she looked at me and the way she stretched her words, I was fairly sure she was drunk or high.  Once she handed us drinks, she never came back. She walked past us about 6 times. We did all the regular "we're ready" signals (closed our menus, unrolled our napkins, even made eye contact with the server). This blonde girl just kept walking right past us despite looking me in the eye and smiling. By about 8:15, we debated leaving. At this point, another couple came in and sat down; the moment they sat down, she whipped over to them with water and took their orders. That's when we got up and walked out.  On our way out the door, the host WHO JUST SEATED US said "thanks for coming, have a good night!". We looked back and told him, "we didn't get served. You know we just came in, right?". He looked as us very confused, almost as though he was as high as the blonde server. From 8 to 8:15, they only seated us and that one other couple who came in. Dude...like, you seated two tables, how the hell did you forget us that quickly?  I lived in Gainesville for several years, I've been here several times and never had a bad experience before. I came to visit from Houston and wanted to eat here because I've missed it, but wound up at Boca Fiesta instead. I've tried calling to discuss this matter, but nobody has been available to speak with me.  Very disappointed, guys.

Food was pretty good. 2 rolls for $9 at lunch is a great price. The ginger dressing was a little different than you would normally have at an Asian place. It was creamy? Like it had milk in it. The sushi was neat and good- for the most part. One of my roles had a slightly off taste but not in a bad way. Just unusual for a tuna avacado roll.  Restaurant is okay. Good location. Bathroom is having some issues and service is a little slow. But still, it was $9 for two rolls a soup and salad so it really turned out okay. I wouldn't go in the evening and pay full price though.

Best tempora lobster roll in Gainesville!  Very consistent sushi, and full bar. Service is very good with attention to the table.  Atmosphere good for conversation for small groups and couples date night.  Sit near the window and people watch. Ask sushi chef for recommendations.
We liked the food. Sushi rolls were good. Recommend the Golden Apple and Rainbow roll. Good service. Ask for a table, though. Booths are too low.
Decent food.  Relaxing atmosphere. Amazing tea.
Absolutely wonderful service and food.
Lots of teas. Get the bento box upgrade, trust me.
good food, quick & pleasant service

I have eaten here many times over the years. Tonight after a movie at the Hippodrome we had a nice meal, though the waiter was a bit unfriendly. At the end of our meal he brought my wife and I separate checks, without asking how we wanted to pay. We are two women and he just assumed therefore we were not together. We asked him to bring us one chack, which he did, and when we offered advice to expand his concept of the universe and recommend he ask customers instead of making assumptions, he was defensive and even more unfriendly. He's the general manager. We won't be back and recommend that LGBTQ people dine elsewhere.

Wait time was kinda lengthy (30ish minutes) for an empty resturant, servers were hard to find, even to ask for a simple water refill. Food was otherwise great. It's a good date setting too, a little on the pricey side.
Great food, reasonable prices, service was ok, but the bathroom was gross. Dark, dirty and the floors were sticky!
Great sushi!!!
Don't be fooled by appearances. We went past this place many times before we checked it out. This is our new favorite place in town.
Great sushi bar. Good ambience.
Great food. Good vibe.
Very relaxing environment and great food! Their curry dishes are very tasty and they have a nice selection of sushi and plenty of vegetarian options!

If I was basing this just on food they’d have 4 stars. Although all I’ve had is easy sushi it’s been executed very well. Unfortunately their customer service is sub par at best. Both in house and attempting to order over the phone. Also don’t order from bite squad as they simply make their orders last priority.
Love this extremely reasonable, upscale restaurant
Well priced, friendly staff.

The staff wasn't the nicest and the food wasn't the best. It's a nice place to try if you haven't, but if you're debating between the salmon and the steak, go for the steak. I know Liquid Ginger has great food, but some things are bland. The green tea ice cream was a winner though!
Great food
Very average food, small rice serving (like getting only one piece of toast).  Serve was good, friendly.  Men's restroom like a dungeon (dark), but clean.  My better half liked it more.

The food here was delicious, plenty of vegetarian and vegan options on the menu. We visited at 6pm on a Friday night and had to wait 20 minutes for a table, but I would have to say the food was well worth it. Plus the wait time there was no longer than any of those other places in downtown would be at that time. The restaurant was clean and the staff were friendly and attentive despite how busy the establishment was. Will definitely come back!

I was over there with my family for hurricane Irma and very excited to find it open. We ordered basil chiken, tuna and tofu. Unfortunately chicken and tuna tasted fake and tofu was barely ok. Soup and Salad were good. Prices were very reasonable.

I placed an order for one simple hand roll (salmon and avocado) that took them over 25 minutes to serve me. They definitely need to get their kitchen streamlined, because thats ridiculous. Flavor and quality was okay.
Great food good service moderate prices
The muscles are delicious. Sushi is always fresh.
I've always thought of Liquid Ginger as a good date night location. But turns out they also have great, inexpensive lunch specials.

I love Liquid Ginger.  I was with 6 other women and we celebrated my birthday.  The atmosphere is quiet, so it is possible to talk with your dinner companions without raising your voice.  So pleasant.  Our server was good except she decided the serving of the fish Ordered was too small and, without asking me, she held up my dinner while another, larger portion was cooked.  As a result everyone at the table was eating well before my dinner finally arrived.  The smaller fish was also included and it would have been just fine.  In fact, I ate the smaller fish and took the larger one home.  My birthday dessert was wonderful...a yummy cheesecake that was plentiful enough for good sharing.  I had a bento box and everything was very good.  Everyone else seemed pleased with their food and we will be back.
Nothing tasted fresh. Cheap ingredients cheap food
Liquid Ginger is my go to when I am downtown. The food and service are consistently excellent. The atmosphere is somewhat quiet, so it is a great place for a business meeting or for date night.
It was really nice  -- I got the bento option and it was very good. The vegetarian options seem really good too. The tea selection was very varied.
Good Restaurant! Bit cheaper.

I've been going here for over 10 years (more regularly for the last 5) and I've never had a bad experience beyond a long wait during the lunchtime rush. My family & I went to Liquid Ginger for lunch on a Sunday @ 12:30. We we ushered to the basement seating area where the floor was dirty, and the vacuum stood in full view, unused. Once we were seated, we then waited twenty minutes to be seen by a waitress. Then, after waiting a half-hour for any food to arrive  - and still nothing...we walked out. Wish I could rate more than 5 stars. This place is so unique and authentic. I am absurdly satisfied with my visit. The tea is cheap and very delicious. It's brought out in its very own cast iron pot. Let me mention how comfortable the booths are too and come with pillows to prop up behind you. The miso soup is the best I've ever had in my life and I like to frequent Asian restrauants. Their ginger dressing salad was exceptional. I ordered the filet mignon and holy moly I was in love. My boyfriend got two sushi rolls, both he ate each bite with a small orgasmic moan because it was so good. Definitely recommend this place.  I will be back.

Description: I came here a few weeks ago for lunch. A friend of mine said their food was pretty good and worth trying so I figured why not. From where it's located to its name, Liquid Ginger, sounds like a cool fusion hip restaurant if I had to take a wild guess. Although the interior is nice and somewhat ideal to bring a date, it wasn't what I was expecting. The place looked a tad worn out and generic. My guess is that the restaurant has looked the same for a long time. Again, nothing wrong just not what I expected when I heard the name.  Food & Service: I will say their lunch menu is very affordable and quite reasonable. A lot of their lunch specials came with a soup and salad, not bad. It seems to be a solid place for people getting a bite to eat on their lunch break. Not sure about their dinner. Anyways, my experience turned a bit sour from there. After getting my water, my waiter didn't come back for awhile to take my order. Granted he was busy but it took longer than usual. I ordered the coconut curry with shrimp. Soup and salad were very basic. It's nice that they come with the meal but it's just filler food in my opinion. The curry was eh. Flavor wasn't bad but it was slightly watery and wasn't very hot. Rice portion was a tad stingy. The vegetables and shrimp weren't good though. Not well seasoned and tasted like packaged food. The shrimp was way too rubbery, definitely overcooked. I was in and out pretty quick because I had to work. The waiter was kind enough to bring me a box and my check swiftly so I could leave.  Final Thoughts: Overall, I'll still give the place 3 stars because I didn't have a terrible experience but it definitely won't be memorable. There's a chance I'll come here again for lunch because of the prices though. I'll stick to something else next time. I've heard their dinner is not bad though? I'll do a possible updated review in the future. Oh! I heard they do have some good tea though, also something to check out maybe.

Nice enough atmosphere but I've had better sushi. The sake was great and that helped but the sushi rice lacked the sweet vinegar flavor that I really like in sushi. The fish and other ingredients that went into the rolls were nice and good but, sushi is more than just those it is also special attention to the rice. Tea was good. Service, hot and cold. Great when I could see our waitress, bad when she was no where to be found.

My boyfriend and I went here yesterday for dinner. We ordered quite a few dishes and everything was okay for the most part until we got to the sushi. It was really mushy and soggy and just overall greasy from the mayonnaise. We ate a few pieces in a hope that the roll would redeem itself but it did not. I told the waitress that I didn't like the roll and asked if it could be taken off the bill. She was very nice and told me they could make a new roll. We were already done with our meal and didn't want to wait for a new roll so I asked if she could ask the manager if the roll could be taken off the bill. She came back with a menu and stated that he said they would gladly make us a new roll but would not remove the roll from the bill. I asked if I could speak with the manager directly. The manager came over and we had a dispute about the quality of the food and removing it from the bill. This dispute lasted for several minutes and in front of numerous other customers. After several minutes I gave up the argument because I was uncomfortable and wanted to leave and he finally decided they would remove the cost of the sushi. Overall it was an awful experience and I would not return. The whole situation was completely unprofessional.

Most of my experiences at Liquid Ginger have been okay. There is one waitress who is a total sweetheart and I will usually ask to be seated in her area. Last night, we were seated next to a couple who had a problem with one of the items they ordered. We overheard the discussion because after they politely asked to send the barely touched food item back, the manager refused to remove the item from the bill. They asked to speak with the manager directly and he publicly argued with them refusing to take the item off their bill. From what I heard, they had good reason to remove it because they had already finished the rest of their food and the sushi item was of very poor quality. If I were the manager, I would immediately take the small loss to keep the customer happy. It was clear they were dissatisfied with the quality of the food and not trying to cheat the restaurant. It made myself and I imagine the others around very uncomfortable. Very disappointed with this experience and will not be back.

We finally stopped by after its remodel and couldn't wait to try the new menu items like sushi. We sat and started reminiscing of our old time in Gainesville. We got our soup and then our salad. Halfway through my salad I was about to take a bite and noticed something funny. I thought it was just a discoloration from a lettuce leaf until I saw a leg and then wings and the head. Yep there was a fly that had drowned in the ginger dressing. I was disgusted. Told our waiter and he just looked at the fork., and offered me a new salad. Of course I didn't want one I just wanted to leave but I wanted my sushi. We got our check and nothing was discounted and no apology was offered. I asked him to speak with a manager and he was the manager. He said that it wasn't a fly. Excuse me sir!!! They were wings and legs and a fly body!!!! I know what I was about to eat... He basically called me a liar. That being said not coming back. I've managed restaurants before and this is not how you manage a situation like this.

Food and atmosphere are both amazing! Service can be a little slow, even when the restaurant isn't that busy, so I always try to budget an extra hour or so when I go (especially for large parties) but I feel that it's well worth the wait. Great wine selection and drink menu as well. This is definitely a place I bring friends and family from out of town!
